b'Happy Thanksgiving from all of us at The Fresh Market. :turkey::pie::sparkles:\xe2\x81\xa0\n\xe2\x81\xa0\nWe hope your day is full of thanks, family and food! :green_heart:'

b'Cook Like a Chef this holiday season with great tips from Chef Jarrod! :man_cook:\xe2\x81\xa0
\xe2\x81\xa0
:sparkles: Br\xc3\xbbl\xc3\xa9e Your Pie + Make It \xc3\xa0 la Mode :sparkles:\xe2\x81\xa0
Break out that br\xc3\xbbl\xc3\xa9e torch that you\xe2\x80\x99ve only used once and torch a generous portion of granulated sugar over your pie before serving.\xe2\x81\xa0
\xe2\x81\xa0
Let the top cool just slightly so you get that nice crack, then top it with ice cream.\xe2\x81\xa0
\xe2\x81\xa0
This irresistible combination will make you wonder why you\xe2\x80\x99ve never had this before! :pie::ice_cream:\xe2\x81\xa0
\xe2\x81\xa0
:green_circle: FOR MORE TIPS: [link in bio] :link:\xe2\x81\xa0'

b'Enjoy the Thanksgiving feast without feeling stuffed! :turkey::fork_and_knife_with_plate_selector::pie:\xe2\x81\xa0
\xe2\x81\xa0
Follow these great tips from Meghan Flynn, our communications director who is also a registered dietitian nutritionist:\xe2\x81\xa0
\xe2\x81\xa0
:glowing_star: #1. Pack on the Protein: For appetizers, go for shrimp cocktail or smoked salmon. You can also snack on a handful of nuts to keep you full.\xe2\x81\xa0
\xe2\x81\xa0
:glowing_star: #2. Satisfy Your Sweet Tooth: This might be your only chance to have pumpkin or pecan pie all year, so there\xe2\x80\x99s no reason to pass on dessert. Curate your plate with a tasting portion of the desserts you love the most.\xe2\x81\xa0
\xe2\x81\xa0
:glowing_star: #3. Swap This for That: Make traditional dishes lighter with simple swaps. For example, halve the butter in the mashed potatoes and add plain Greek yogurt for extra creaminess and protein.\xe2\x81\xa0
\xe2\x81\xa0
:green_circle: FOR MORE GREAT TIPS: [link in bio] :link:\xe2\x81\xa0'

b':turkey: LET\xe2\x80\x99S TALK TURKEY :turkey:\xe2\x81\xa0
\xe2\x81\xa0
Keep it simple and carve in the kitchen rather than carving the bird at the table. We like to remove all the meat from the turkey and then slice it for easier serving. \xe2\x81\xa0
\xe2\x81\xa0
:green_circle: MORE TURKEY TIPS: [link in bio] :link:\xe2\x81\xa0'

b'Thanksgiving is quickly approaching! :turkey:\xe2\x81\xa0
\xe2\x81\xa0
Looking for a last-minute recipe idea? Elevate your plate with goat cheese!\xe2\x81\xa0
\xe2\x81\xa0
Instead of topping your sweet potatoes with marshmallows, roast them up in a casserole dish loaded with smoky paprika-infused butter and fresh chopped rosemary.\xe2\x81\xa0
\xe2\x81\xa0
Once they become tender, sprinkle them with tangy crumbles of goat cheese and finish under the broiler until the cheese gets soft and melty. Voil\xc3\xa0! \xe2\x81\xa0
\xe2\x81\xa0
:green_circle: SHOP INGREDIENTS: [link in bio] :link:\xe2\x81\xa0'

b'Halloumi is one of our favorite summer cheeses because it\xe2\x80\x99s best enjoyed grilled! :fire:\xe2\x81\xa0
\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\x81\xa0
This mild but tangy, made by hand Greek cheese is comprised of cow, sheep and goat milk cheeses. Its firm texture and high melting point make it perfect for the grill. Check out some of our tips for easy grilling! :light_bulb:\xe2\x81\xa0
\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\x81\xa0
GUIDE TO GRILLING HALLOUMI:\xe2\x81\xa0
:sparkle_selector: Be sure to oil your grill grates well, otherwise the halloumi will stick.\xe2\x81\xa0
:sparkle_selector: Slice your halloumi into \xc2\xbc-1/2-inch thick slabs before grilling or cut into chunks and thread onto kabob skewers.\xe2\x81\xa0
:sparkle_selector: Halloumi only needs a couple of minutes per side on the grill, just enough to sear it and achieve that crisp exterior and melty interior.\xe2\x81\xa0
:sparkle_selector: Serve with sweet, tart and savory components like fruit, fresh herbs and crunchy nuts to balance out the saltiness of the cheese.\xe2\x81\xa0
\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\x81\xa0
Have you had halloumi before? Let us know in the comments if you\xe2\x80\x99re excited to try this cheese on the grill over the summer!'

b"What Makes a Tomato an Heirloom?\xe2\x81\xa0
\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\x81\xa0
:tomato: The Seeds: Farmers pick the seeds from the plants that produced the best fruit season after season, focusing on size, juiciness, freshness, shape, color and flavor.\xe2\x81\xa0
\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\x81\xa0
:tomato: The Pollination Process: Heirlooms are open-pollinated, meaning they are pollinated by nature or by hand and reproduce from their seed.\xe2\x81\xa0
\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\x81\xa0
:tomato: The Variety: Seeds passed down through several farming generations, or are at least 50 years old.\xe2\x81\xa0
\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\x81\xa0

:cut_of_meat: Season your steak, then let it sit at room temperature 15-30 minutes. This helps it cook more evenly.\xe2\x81\xa0

b'Whip up this quick and easy Pasta with Tuna, Capers and Lemon recipe with pantry staples for a delicious dinner in no time!
\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80
INGREDIENTS:
:sparkle_selector: 1 (4 oz) can @portofinotuna Solid White Albacore Tuna in Extra Virgin Olive Oil
:sparkle_selector: \xc2\xbc c @tessemaes Pantry Classic Italian Dressing
:sparkle_selector: 2 tbsp The Fresh Market Capers
:sparkle_selector: Zest and juice of one small lemon
:sparkle_selector: 1 (8 oz) box @eatbanza Penne Pasta
:sparkle_selector: \xc2\xbc c flat-leaf parsley, chopped
\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80
DIRECTIONS:
Combine tuna, dressing, capers and lemon zest and juice in a large bowl. Cook pasta according to package instructions (but be sure to generously salt your pasta water and do not rinse after draining). After draining, immediately add hot pasta to the bowl with the tuna. Use a large spoon or spatula to toss everything together, coating the pasta and breaking up the tuna. Add the parsley and toss some more. Serve immediately.'

b'Supreme your citrus! :tangerine: These are citrus segments with all the peel, pith and membranes removed, so you\xe2\x80\x99re left with tender citrus fruit with none of the bitterness. Check out the step-by-step instructions below: :down_arrow_selector:
\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80
:tangerine: Slice It Right: Using a sharp chef\xe2\x80\x99s knife, slice about 1/2 inch from the top and bottom of your citrus fruit.
\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80
:tangerine: Stand Up Straight: Stand fruit vertically on the work surface.
\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80
:tangerine: Peel Away: Working from top to bottom, cut off the peel where it meets the flesh, following the curve of the fruit. Turn fruit and continue until no pith or peel remains.
\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80
:tangerine: Check Yourself: Look over your work! Be sure to trim away any remaining pith.
\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80
:tangerine: Let It Go: Working over a bowl to catch the juices, hold the fruit in one hand. Cut between each membrane to release the supreme, and let it fall into the bowl.
\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80
:tangerine: One More Squeeze: Do not discard just yet! Squeeze the membrane in your hand to extract any remaining juice.'

b'Life is a cabernet! :wine_glass: Did you know our in-house wine experts search high and (merlot) for the best sips at the best price point?

\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80
:wine_glass: @storypointwines Cabernet Sauvignon: This California cab Opens with expressive notes of dark fruit and fragrant baking spices. This robust Cabernet Sauvignon reveals rich layers of blackberry, dark cherry, mint, sage and black tea and finishes with unique oak signatures of cocoa, molasses and gingerbread.
\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80
:wine_glass: @hahnwines SLH Pinot Noir: Aged for 11 months in French oak barrels, this Pinot Noir that opens with alluring aromas of black cherry and dark currant. What follows are intense black fruit flavors balanced by ripe red plums and a hint of allspice.
\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80
:wine_glass: @michaeldavidwinery Petite Petit: This full-bodied Petite Sirah and Petit Verdot blend is made in Lodi, California. The wine spends 9 months in French oak and 7 months in neutral oak. It boasts black fruit flavors and a smoky, aromatic finish.
\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80
:wine_glass: @bodegagarzon Reserva Tannat: This wine is made with estate-grown grapes from Uruguay and has been aged for 6-12 months in French oak barrels. It features notes of crushed boysenberry, red plum, toasted herbs, and a faintly saline, marine note.
\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80
:wine_glass: @atozwineworks Chardonnay: A to Z Chardonnay dances on the palate, alive with flavors of citrus fruits, green apple and starfruit. There is a grapefruit pith note to the finish, along with a linear minerality that carries through for quite some time after tasting.'

b"Make our crowd-pleasing Low Country Shrimp Boil! :shrimp: Be sure to click the 'save' icon to reference this post later. :light_bulb:
\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80
INGREDIENTS:
:sparkle_selector: \xc2\xbe c Old Bay seasoning
:sparkle_selector: \xc2\xbc c white vinegar
:sparkle_selector: 2 tbsp kosher salt
:sparkle_selector: 2 lb red new potatoes, halved
:sparkle_selector: 2 Andouille sausage, cut into 2-in pieces
:sparkle_selector: 12 ears of corn, husked, cleaned and cut into thirds
:sparkle_selector: 3 lbs (21-25 ct) Wild American Shrimp
\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80
DIRECTIONS:
In a large stockpot, bring 6 qts water, Old Bay Seasoning, vinegar and salt to a boil. Add potatoes and sausage; cook for 10 minutes. Add corn; cook for 5-7 minutes, or until corn becomes tender. Stir in shrimp and cook until shrimp are pink, about 5 minutes more. Drain immediately and serve."

b'Go ahead and hit the "save" icon :winking_face:. Our Kumquat Ricotta Toast recipe is the ultimate unexpected flavor combination and perfect for easy snacking or quick get-togethers.
\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80
INGREDIENTS:
:sparkle_selector: 1 sourdough baguette, sliced diagonally into about \xc2\xbd-in thick slices
:sparkle_selector: 1 (16 oz) container whole milk ricotta cheese
:sparkle_selector: 1 pt kumquats, washed and thinly sliced
:sparkle_selector: 1 (12 oz) bottle @mikeshothoney
:sparkle_selector: \xc2\xbd c caramelized walnuts, roughly chopped
\xe2\xa0\x80\xe2\xa0\x80
DIRECTIONS:
Preheat broiler. Place bread slices on sheet pan broil until lightly toasted, about 5 minutes. Spread 2-3 tbsp ricotta on each piece of toast, followed by sliced kumquats. Drizzle with desired amount of honey and top with walnuts.'
